-- South African Coal Export Prices Decline Most in Four Weeks
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-01-16T11:09:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-16/south-african-coal-export-prices-decline-most-in-four-weeks.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, declined the most in four weeks.  Prices (CLSPSARB)  fell 76 cents, or 0.7 percent, to an average $105.89
a metric ton in the week ended Jan. 13, according to data on
Bloomberg from IHS McCloskey. That’s the steepest decrease since
Dec. 16. The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which
excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  